1
00:00:00,867 --> 00:00:03,333
I am Kotoko Aihara of Class F.

2
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:06,267
Could you please read this letter?

3
00:00:06,967 --> 00:00:09,967
-No thank you.
-Rejecting Kotoko? I will punish him.

4
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:11,767
This means a war.

5
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:15,167
When you move, luck may turn
in your favor.

6
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,000
A shooting star?

7
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:22,400
It got hit by a shooting star?

8
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>I ended up living with a family of my</i>
<i>dad's best friend.</i>

9
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:31,967
<i>-But it turned out...</i>
-What's wrong with you, Kotoko?

10
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:34,333
Hi, I am--

11
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:38,767
<i>It turned out to be a family of Naoki</i>
<i>Irie, whom I really liked.</i>

12
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:42,467
Tell no one that we live together. Do not
talk to me at school at all.

13
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,067
You don't need to humiliate me that much.

14
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:47,133
I don't like a stupid girl.

15
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:51,433
I will beat Naoki Irie with term-end
exams.

16
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,033
-Give it to me.
-We have a week until the exams.

17
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:57,000
-Help me study.
-Kotoko may be

18
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:59,900
much more awesome than I think.

19
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:02,467
I can't believe it. 100th?

20
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:07,200
I suspect that her new house holds some
secrets.

21
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:10,967
What is this?

22
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:13,833
Do you live at Naoki Irie's house?

23
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,100
-Aihara.
-What?

24
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:17,500
Just come.

25
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:20,400
<i>Our secret of living together was out.</i>

26
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:22,933
<i>Everybody in our school is gossiping</i>
<i>about us.</i>

27
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,867
What are your friends thinking?

28
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:32,433
Since you like me, it would be okay for
you, but this bothers me a lot.

29
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:37,033
Do not disturb my life anymore.

30
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,333
I...

31
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:49,167
am crying? Why?

32
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:59,533
<i>Since Irie had rejected me flatly,</i>

33
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:07,133
<i>I didn't think that I would care how</i>
<i>he treated me anymore.</i>

34
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:12,233
<i>Then why am I crying?</i>

35
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,067
After all...

36
00:02:37,033 --> 00:02:40,767
I think I still love him.

37
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,033
Kotoko, you are so late.

38
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:55,367
-I was worried about you.
-Sorry.

39
00:02:55,533 --> 00:02:59,967
I should have called you earlier.
I'm really sorry.

40
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:40,300
<i>This is the first love letter</i>
<i>I wrote in my life.</i>

41
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:45,933
<i>But this love letter has no reader.</i>

42
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,767
No thank you.

43
00:03:49,933 --> 00:03:53,333
<i>I know he is a jerk, but...</i>

44
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,767
<i>I still love him. Why?</i>

45
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:08,733
Hey, take a bath.

46
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:17,233
I'm coming in.
My mom wants you to take a bath.

47
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:35,200
<i>Dear Mr. Irie.</i>
<i>I am Kotoko Aihara of Class F.</i>

48
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:38,733
<i>You may not know me.</i>

49
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,200
<i>But I know you well.</i>

50
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:48,000
<i>I've been in love with you for two years</i>
<i>since the entrance ceremony.</i>

51
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:51,933
<i>I felt like I was struck</i>
<i>by a shooting star</i>

52
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:54,500
<i>when I saw you for the first time.</i>

53
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:58,733
<i>This special feeling</i>
<i>has stayed in my heart.</i>

54
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,567
<i>I love</i>

55
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,467
<i>you.</i>

56
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:09,500
MISCHIEVOUS KISS

57
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:17,100
{\an8}MORNING COFFEE
IS THE AROMA OF LOVE!?

58
00:07:42,767 --> 00:07:45,300
Good morning.

59
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:47,133
Good morning, Kotoko.

60
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:52,367
You overslept as usual. Why don't you
wake up early to help her?

61
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,567
-I'm sorry.
-Don't worry.

62
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:57,367
Neither of my sons will help me at all.

63
00:07:57,533 --> 00:08:00,600
-Have breakfast.
-Okay.

64
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:05,000
Bon appetite.

65
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,033
Hey, Kotoko.

66
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,667
Can you leave school early today?

67
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,233
Sure, but why?

68
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:21,400
I want to pay them back
for their kindness.

69
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:25,200
I would like to cook dinner
for them tonight.

70
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:27,833
-So I want you to help me.
-I see.

71
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,100
That's right.
Your restaurant is closed today.

72
00:08:30,267 --> 00:08:32,700
Mr. Aihara, don't be bothered.

73
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:35,067
I just want to show you my appreciation.

74
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:39,367
Ai-chan is a great chef, so I can't wait.

75
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:42,400
Right, Naoki and Yuki?

76
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:44,433
You are right.

77
00:08:45,367 --> 00:08:47,800
I'm done. See you, everyone.

78
00:08:47,967 --> 00:08:51,067
-Have a great day.
-Have a great day.

79
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:54,200
Kotoko, you have to leave, too.

80
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,900
What?

81
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,833
You have bread crumb on the face.

82
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:34,567
What was that?

83
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,400
HIGH SCHOOL AFFILIATED
TO TONAN UNIVERSITY

84
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:49,267
-Stairs.
-Watch your step.

85
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:54,467
You are in my way.
To be honest, this is very annoying.

86
00:09:55,467 --> 00:10:00,200
This is for you.
I am protecting you from Irie.

87
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:03,267
What?! Irie?

88
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:08,633
I will be fine.
He doesn't like me at all.

89
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:12,233
He told me unequivocally
not to talk to him at school.

90
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,600
Clear.

91
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:19,267
-Roger.
-Look.

92
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:25,133
Is that the girl who lives at your place?
What are they doing?

93
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,967
I don't care.

94
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:39,600
Spy on Irie's house?

95
00:10:39,767 --> 00:10:41,567
You are nuts, Kin-chan.

96
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:46,567
But you two are also curious about them,
aren't you?

97
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:48,500
Well, I guess.

98
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:50,567
That's the house.

99
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:58,533
Huge!

100
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:05,167
Walk stealthily. Walk stealthily.

101
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:17,833
If Irie finds us, he will be mad.

102
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,233
Here she is.

103
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:26,767
-Kotoko!
-Yes.

104
00:11:28,633 --> 00:11:32,900
-Can't see anything.
-The cap is on.

105
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:42,100
Wow. Everything looks so delicious.

106
00:11:42,267 --> 00:11:46,400
Very impressive, Ai-chan.

107
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:49,600
Wait. What is this?

108
00:11:51,233 --> 00:11:56,800
It is deep-fried tofu I made.

109
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:59,767
It may not look good, but it is delicious.

110
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:02,600
-I don't want it.
-Me, either.

111
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:06,633
Naoki and Yuki, watch your mouth.

112
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:09,667
You two are rude.
Let's have a seat.

113
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,767
Damn you! You refused Kotoko's
homemade dish?

114
00:12:16,933 --> 00:12:20,833
Calm down, Kin-chan.
They may see you.

115
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:30,200
Then I will eat Kotoko's dish.

116
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:34,433
If I eat it, you two can eat it, right?

117
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,667
This is terrible.

118
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:58,833
I knew it.

119
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:03,100
No, no. This is delicious.

120
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:05,967
Iri-chan, be honest. That's okay.

121
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:12,533
She has never been good at cooking.
I can't believe that she is my daughter.

122
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:16,600
I must wonder whether someone
will take her as his wife.

123
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:20,467
-I'm sorry.
-Don't worry.

124
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:23,267
We like her. We will take her.

125
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:32,567
What did she just say?

126
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:39,533
I'm saying that you should marry Naoki.

127
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:44,333
No! I'm against it.

128
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,633
It's not your decision.

129
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,800
It's my life. Don't play with it.

130
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:54,867
Really? I really think that Kotoko
is your type.

131
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,067
Am I?

132
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:57,300
No way.

133
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:00,733
You are not my type at all.

134
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,533
I don't want to marry you, either.

135
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:10,233
Good. I'm glad that Kotoko said that.

136
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:17,500
Is that so? Then why did you give me such
a passionate message?

137
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,900
"How do you do, Irie?

138
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:25,900
I am Kotoko Aihara of Class F.

139
00:14:26,067 --> 00:14:29,967
You may not know me, but I know you
well.

140
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:34,567
I have been in love with you, since--"

141
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:37,567
How dare you?

142
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:42,533
-What a jerk! Did you see my letter?
-You wrote it to me, didn't you?

143
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:46,567
-You don't need to memorize it.
-That's not my fault.

144
00:14:46,733 --> 00:14:48,900
How dare you say it in front of everyone?

145
00:14:49,067 --> 00:14:51,200
Wait. What's going on?

146
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:56,333
Kotoko, you mean you have been in love
with Naoki?

147
00:14:58,367 --> 00:15:00,100
Did you hear that?

148
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,700
Tell it to everyone.

149
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,867
I wrote a love letter.

150
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,833
Is that true?

151
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:26,567
Then my fantasy

152
00:15:26,733 --> 00:15:29,367
can be a reality.

153
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:32,633
But that was before
we started living together.

154
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:35,900
-Right now I'm not--
-Don't say that.

155
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:38,900
You may fall in love with him again.
What do you think, honey?

156
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:43,900
Well, if you two like each other,
I'm fine.

157
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,367
Hold it!

158
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,167
Open it!

159
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,900
Who are those kids?

160
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:57,300
Kin-chan?

161
00:15:57,467 --> 00:15:59,467
Kotoko, open the door.

162
00:15:59,633 --> 00:16:04,000
They are my classmates.

163
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:11,100
What the hell are you doing here?

164
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:15,467
Sorry, but Kin-chan really wants to know
how you are doing here.

165
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:17,533
Coming in?

166
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:21,000
Irie is a man, whether he is
a genius or not.

167
00:16:21,167 --> 00:16:24,933
Who knows if he may get interested in
you in the future. See. I was right.

168
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:27,800
I will punish him for what he said.

169
00:16:27,967 --> 00:16:30,667
-Who the hell are you?
-What?

170
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:37,333
Hello, everyone of Irie Family.
How do you do?

171
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:42,700
I am Kinnosuke Ikezawa aka Kin-chan.
I'm Kotoko's classmate.

172
00:16:42,867 --> 00:16:44,500
It means that you are dumb, too.

173
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:47,667
-What did you say?
-Watch your mouth, Yuki.

174
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:53,133
Kotoko and I are in an intimate
relationship.

175
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:55,600
Kin-chan, stop your nonsense.

176
00:16:55,767 --> 00:16:59,100
Kotoko, you are very popular
among boys, huh?

177
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:02,067
-That's right.
-I'm really sorry.

178
00:17:02,233 --> 00:17:06,700
That's why I don't want you
to flirt with her.

179
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:11,967
Marriage? It's not funny at all.
Understand, Mr. Irie?

180
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,333
You never know.

181
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:18,233
What do you mean by that?

182
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,800
Our feelings are complicated.

183
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:25,600
I don't like her today,
but I may like her tomorrow.

184
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:30,833
What? After all, you like Kotoko,
don't you?

185
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:36,700
Who knows. But remember
that she likes me, not you.

186
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:41,933
I'm going to my room, so have fun.

187
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:47,100
<i>What was that?</i>
<i>What did he mean by that?</i>

188
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:55,067
<i>Could it mean...</i>
<i>Do I have a hope?</i>

189
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:58,167
<i>Is that what he meant?</i>

190
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:06,133
<i>In the meantime, our last summer break</i>

191
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:08,467
<i>is about to begin.</i>

192
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:15,100
I wish I can make some wonderful
memories during the last summer break.

193
00:18:15,267 --> 00:18:17,533
But we have to prepare
for the college entrance exam.

194
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,567
-I know that, but...
-I know what you mean.

195
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:24,600
All we do during the break
is our homework? It's sad.

196
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:33,400
Kotoko, you are a lucky one.
You can be with him all summer long.

197
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:35,033
Nothing will happen.

198
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:39,667
Who knows.
He was so passionate the other day.

199
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:42,933
He was just carried away by the argument.

200
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:47,967
You may be right. He didn't even
touch the dish you cooked.

201
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:52,400
That's because I'm not good at cooking.

202
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:57,300
You are missing the point.

203
00:18:57,467 --> 00:19:00,967
Men can't resist a dish
cooked by women they love.

204
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:03,200
It doesn't matter how terrible it is.

205
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:05,367
That's right. You live with him.

206
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:08,067
You can find a way to make him
appreciate your cooking.

207
00:19:08,233 --> 00:19:10,033
That could be

208
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:13,133
the best memory of your summer.

209
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,533
My homemade dish, huh?

210
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:26,100
I'm so worried.

211
00:19:26,267 --> 00:19:29,467
But I can't spy on their house every day.
On the other hand, Irie

212
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:32,200
can be with Kotoko during the break.

213
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:35,900
It's true that women tend to fall in love
with someone close.

214
00:19:36,067 --> 00:19:40,000
Shut up! You are not helping.

215
00:19:40,167 --> 00:19:42,333
Bro, don't give up.

216
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:46,567
You should stay close to Kotoko
as much as possible.

217
00:19:55,767 --> 00:20:01,467
FIRST DAY OF SUMMER BREAK

218
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,433
Good morning, everyone.

219
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,700
Good morning.

220
00:20:18,867 --> 00:20:21,067
Kotoko, you don't have school anymore,
do you?

221
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:26,567
Well, for some reason,

222
00:20:26,733 --> 00:20:29,967
I have to go to school.

223
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:33,133
Why? This is summer break.

224
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:39,433
Well, because... What can I say...

225
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:43,267
-Yuki, answer the door, please.
-Okay.

226
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,667
Yes?

227
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:53,533
<i>Hi, Irie Family!</i>
<i>Good morning.</i>

228
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:57,900
<i>I'm here to pick up Kotoko</i>
<i>for mandatory summer school.</i>

229
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:01,400
Mandatory summer school?

230
00:21:01,567 --> 00:21:03,667
But you ranked 100th
in the last exam.

231
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:10,633
That was the term-end exam.

232
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:15,233
I didn't do well with the mid-term.

233
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:22,333
I wonder how bad your grade was
before the term-end exam. You are dumb.

234
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,400
Shut up.

235
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:29,233
See you later.

236
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,467
All the students from Class F are here.

237
00:21:36,633 --> 00:21:40,333
This looks like a regular class.

238
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:44,967
Listen up. Let me be clear.
You all are on the borderline

239
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:49,967
between going on to
Tonan University or not.

240
00:21:51,067 --> 00:21:55,233
Including Aihara, who ranked 100th in the
term-end exam.

241
00:21:55,400 --> 00:22:00,600
That's why I want you to work hard
in summer school.

242
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:04,567
So-called "summer school of hell"
starts now.

243
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:07,300
Keep in mind that this summer
is a crucial time.

244
00:22:09,967 --> 00:22:16,200
Now we have to forget about making
good memories of summer.

